{"TopicId":207078,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Is there a mod that adds physics to planets?","CreatedByName":"Hadron27","CreatedById":199904,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-28T21:05:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Hadron27","CreatedById":199904,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-28T21:05:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike, i saw a few videos on youtube like this one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022150\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/8DF4LgYl5DM?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut i cant seem to find a mod like this that actually makes the moons get ejected or anything.. And ive tried principia but it doesnt do anything to my knowledge, unless theres a config that i havent seen yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-28T21:15:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPrincipia is what you want. You didn\u0027t install it correctly if it doesn\u0027t do anything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does modify the Joolian system so that planets do not get ejected. It makes it a stable system, so if you are expecting it to be unstable, that won\u0027t be the case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-28T21:17:30Z\u0022 title=\u002202/28/2022 09:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 28, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by MechBFP\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hadron27","CreatedById":199904,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-28T21:17:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646082905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184845\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MechBFP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, MechBFP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPrincipia is what you want. You didn\u0027t install it correctly if it doesn\u0027t do anything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI meant the planets getting flung and stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646082905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184845\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MechBFP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, MechBFP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPrincipia is what you want. You didn\u0027t install it correctly if it doesn\u0027t do anything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does modify the Joolian system so that planets do not get ejected. It makes it a stable system, so if you are expecting it to be unstable, that won\u0027t be the case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. is there any way to stop it from modifying the joolian and kerbin system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(i think minmus gets ejected idk)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mateusviccari","CreatedById":188698,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-01T02:09:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646083028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hadron27\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Hadron27 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI meant the planets getting flung and stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. is there any way to stop it from modifying the joolian and kerbin system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(i think minmus gets ejected idk)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I remember right, letting the system run unstable would cause a whole bunch of problems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal Productions","CreatedById":208620,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-01T02:50:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646083028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hadron27\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Hadron27 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(i think minmus gets ejected idk)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMinmus is strategically located on an orbit that it might wobble its orbit but won\u0027t fling to space. Why? Look how far Minmus is from the Mun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646083028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hadron27\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Hadron27 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. is there any way to stop it from modifying the joolian and kerbin system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t know... but like what this person said:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646100589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188698\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mateusviccari\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, mateusviccari said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nletting the system run unstable would cause a whole bunch of problems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-01T03:28:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646083028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199904\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hadron27\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Hadron27 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. is there any way to stop it from modifying the joolian and kerbin system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou would be most likely to get a good answer to that question on the Principia thread, where people who understand that mod hang out:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u00224680\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed564295150\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/162200-wip181-191-1101-1110%E2%80%932-1122%E2%80%933-principia%E2%80%94version-%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B6-%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0-released-2022-02-01%E2%80%94n-body-and-extended-body-gravitation/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:198px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut looking at the code, the stabilization logic is hard coded (and only changes Jool\u0027s moons, not Kerbin\u0027s):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/astronomy/stabilize_ksp_body.hpp#L17-L48\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/astronomy/stabilize_ksp_body.hpp#L17-L48\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nand there does not seem to be an explicit setting to turn it off:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/ksp_plugin/plugin.cpp#L207-L229\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/ksp_plugin/plugin.cpp#L207-L229\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, it does depend on an analysys of the solar system with a \u0022fingerprint\u0022 algorithm to determine if it\u0027s stock, which looks like it serializes their physical properties and then hashes them:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/physics/solar_system_body.hpp#L294-L341\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/physics/solar_system_body.hpp#L294-L341\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/base/fingerprint2011.hpp#L28-L65\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/mockingbirdnest/Principia/blob/5f938415f207138b134b530d56ff8fe28ced8042/base/fingerprint2011.hpp#L28-L65\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nSo if you use Kopernicus to make some small, subtle changes to some planet you don\u0027t care about (e.g., tweak Eeloo\u0027s mass?) to change your solar system\u0027s fingerprint, that might be enough to bypass the stabilizer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hadron27","CreatedById":199904,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-03T19:24:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh thank you guys so much\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try it out later\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T09:32:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224097971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207078\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221646100589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188698\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mateusviccari\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/1/2022 at 3:09 AM, mateusviccari said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I remember right, letting the system run unstable would cause a whole bunch of problems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIIRC, it only causes problems when one body crashes into another. If an unstable body is simply ejected, I think its fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is to say an initial unstable configuration that can stabilize would be tolerated, no?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}